I thought I remembered reading once that if the weapons damage was at least above half of the damage that your pet can do w/o a weapon, that it was beneficial to have one.

So, for example, if your pet hits for 20, give him a weapon with a damage of 11 or better.

I've done some unscientific experiments with my necro.  My level 29 pet when given a 20 damage weapon will routinely hit in the 40's, and occasionally low 50's...which pretty much rocks for a level 29 pet.  Also, bonus is, weapon delay means nothing, as your pets delay overrides.

You can get high damage weapons for cheap in the bazaar...just put in a 5-10pp max and search the 2hb/hs/piercing weapons.  

